article.headline: Villanova 75, Boston College 61
article.linkText: Villanova routs Boston College in key Big East tilt
article.story:
VILLANOVA, Pa. (AP) -- Katie Davis and Trish Juhline scored 16
points apiece to lead No. 22 Villanova over No. 23 Boston College
75-61 Wednesday night.

	   Davis scored 11 of her points in the first half, hitting three
3-pointers along the way for Villanova (16-4, 6-3 Big East).

	   Courtney Mix scored 15 points, pulled down eight rebounds and
had seven assists for Villanova. Kelly Nash came off the bench to
go 3-for-4 from three-point range as the Wildcats built a 40-25
halftime lead.

	   Boston College (15-5, 7-2), which had won four straight, trailed
by double-digits through most of the game before going on a 13-2
run midway through the second half. Becky Gottstein scored nine of
her game-high 19 points in the rally, which cut Villanova's lead to
64-55 with 4:16 remaining, but the Eagles got no closer.

	   Jessalyn Deveny scored 16 for Boston College, which went 0-for-7
from 3-point range.
